textBody: Jabal Ram is a mountain in Jordan. Most authorities give its elevation as 1734 m metres above sea level. It was once thought to be the highest point in Jordan, but SRTM data shows that Jabal Umm al Dami is 1854 m metres above sea level  and therefore higher.
